Entertaining will be an absolute pleasure here. The open plan kitchen features a large central bench for guests to gather around, then spill out to the spacious North-facing deck. An additional bathroom serves the second bedroom, plus there’s the added convenience of a downstairs toilet too. All your needs are taken care of here, with no compromise on space or style. There’s even a car parking space in a secure garage nearby at 17 Federal Street.

This stunning apartment offers a multitude of lifestyle options – a spacious modern home for you and your family; a weekday city pad that lets you balance your life and work commitments. And did I mention the strong and consistent rental income if you’re looking for a solid long term investment?

Title: Edwardian Character, Contemporary Chic

Attributes.Name: location
Attributes.Value: 5/9 Parliament Street, City Centre, Auckland City, Auckland

Body:
A masterful juxtaposition of gorgeous original period character and sleek practical contemporary design, this elegant 2-bedroom residence in Middle Courtville is unique.
 
Along a quiet leafy inner-city street, the much-admired, well-maintained Category 1 Historic Edwardian landmark was completed in 1915. It was Auckland’s first purpose-built block of self-contained apartments, created for women to work in the city while menfolk were away at war.

To enter the beautifully restored foyer is to step back in time. On the floor above, the apartment opens to high ceilings with ornate cornices, stained glass windows, gracious bays, kauri floors and an ornate tiled fireplace. Yet the introduction of tasteful modern amenities makes this home eminently liveable.
The lounge links with ease through glazed French doors to an adjoining formal dining room or second bedroom. The 2 rooms work as one larger space when required. Romantic deep covered balconies overlook the High Court – where you can watch the world go by.

A massive amount of clever designer storage sets the home apart from the others in the block. It is artfully concealed everywhere. An entire wall of floor to ceiling cupboards in the dining room magically flips open to reveal a dazzling LED-lit cocktail bar. Chic minimalist design makes a cool white statement in the kitchen, maximising spatial efficiency with drawers hidden within drawers. Superbly-lit custom solutions are also found in the bedroom. Even the bathroom surprises with its
towering white cupboard and shelving, an inviting clawfoot bath and minimalist spray
shower.

Owners enjoy a substantial communal garden courtyard to the rear of the building and 24/7 residents’ street parking. In a superb location in an established heritage precinct by Old Government House, the University, Albert Park, the CBD and the waterfront. Enjoy the privilege of a rare, very special character home.
